reviews.text:
Tore it up! I got the bourbon bacon burger with tots. Patties were thick, bun was good quality, generous portion of bacon, the sauce and cheese were also fantastic. The onion rings that came on the burger were small and not good, however, I'd make sure to ask for fresh onion rings if you get them. Tots were pretty good, and got a free Oreo shake when I signed up for texts. Shake went down super fast, very smooth, very good.
Owner was there and very courteous, great service and food was quick but not so fast you wonder if it's not fresh. Glad we came!

I was so excited to come here with my friends. I ordered with one of my friends and we both got the wrong order taken out to us. The staff was kind in bringing us new food. Then my friends that did an online order both had to wait over an hour for their food. Upon asking them multiple times where their food was, the staff said they were still working on it. After an hour and a half, they got one of the orders out and it was completely wrong. However we just still ate it because we didn‚Äôt want to wait for a new burger. My other friend asked for his food many more times, and they brought him the wrong food not once but twice. He asked for a refund and they said they don‚Äôt know how to give one. So after 4 wrong orders, I was not happy. Very disappointed in my experience here. I wanted to enjoy it but I don‚Äôt know if I will ever be back.

Ordered at 653. Didn't have our food by 730 and asked the front desk. Staff constantly walked by talking others their food that Ordered after us. Didn't scan the room seeing we had been there for forever not getting our food. Ask for my money back. Shift lead proceeded to "make" our food for 15 more minutes while we waited for our money back. These were made fresh and you can see by the picture the double cheese bacon burger bowl had about a half a hamburger on it and no bacon. Then we get food and 2 out of the 3 things are wrong. We were 1 of 3 people in the restaurant at the time that they screwed up their meal/completely forgot to make it. How the heck does that happen?

I got the bourbon burger, it was amazing! I was really impressed with the quality of the food. The staff was nice and the lobby was clean. I‚Äôll definitely be back!

Just came BACK for my second time! Still amazing quality, and I love the onion rings & tater tots. Highly recommend this place

Good, not great. The meat was tender and juicy, but bland and very under seasoned. Some salt and a proper sear would go a long way! The bacon was just okay as well. Not the crispy texture and flavor I typically prefer.

Fries were alright, but the tater tots were much better. It‚Äôs hard to mess up tots though!

It basically felt like a ‚Äúfancier‚Äù Wendy‚Äôs, and I would go back if the patty was salted and seared better.

recentReviews.text: Super nice employees and the food was really really tasty! It was my first time going but I'll definitely go back for sure!

I rolled up to Wayback Burgers thinking I could outsmart a burger by deconstructing it onto fries. Spoiler: the burger gods were not impressed.
The real MVP? The counter server who answered my ridiculous questions with saint-like patience and actually brought food to our table like some fast-food fairy godmother. In a world of ‚Äúorder 47, come get your sad meal,‚Äù this was refreshingly human.
My brilliant deconstructed burger experiment was‚Ä¶ fine. You know, ‚Äúfine‚Äù like your cousin‚Äôs potato salad ‚Äì edible but missing the magic. Turns out there‚Äôs a reason burgers come pre-assembled. Next time I‚Äôm trusting the engineers and ordering like a normal person.
But the chocolate brownie shake? Pure liquid regret. Despite reading warnings that it was sweeter than a rom-com and runnier than my gym excuses, I ordered it anyway. This shake was so thin I spent more time stirring than drinking, and sweet enough to cause diabetes through osmosis. Should‚Äôve gotten a soda and saved myself the disappointment.
The Verdict: Great service, decent burgers (if you don‚Äôt try to reinvent them), and shakes that are basically chocolate-flavored mistakes. Skip the liquid stuff, stick to the solids, and tip that counter angel and you may get the extra effort you paid for!
Tasted amazing. Reasonable prices. I got the Cajun burger.

I had a great experience the first time I visited this place, which made me excited to return for my son's birthday. Unfortunately, our second visit didn‚Äôt live up to expectations. We were told there would be over an hour wait just to receive our food, and we saw several customers ahead of us getting refunds due to incorrect orders. With everything going on, we decided to leave. It‚Äôs disappointing, especially after such a positive first impression.

Wayback has the best burger you can get. No matter where you get it they‚Äôre all the same quality. This particular wayback is clean, with great friendly staff, the food was hot and fresh. I can‚Äôt say enough about how great the burgers are! And not just the burgers, the sides, the other sandwiches, even the lemonade. I have never had a bad meal here!
The food was really good and was a great price none of their burgers are over $10. I got the bacon cheeseburger which was very good. The service was fast and the food was nice and hot.
Super good food and such a lovely staff.

We ordered online and the food was ready so quickly. I am gluten free and while they don‚Äôt offer GF buns, they do have the bowls- and you can fully customize these. I didn‚Äôt feel left out, especially with the fry base for my bowl! The manager came out it and checked on us, making it feel like a family based and friendly environment. The workers were kind and quick to help. 1000% will be coming back and will be recommending to all of my friends!
Good cheeseburger but I did ask for no tomato and it still came with the tomato. Other than that was yummy and hit the spot

We ordered pickup here for my family of four. The burgers were good, but unfortunately there were more than a few hiccups:

- The burger for my two-year-old had an extra patty.
- One burger was supposed be plain but had everything on it.
- The chili cheese fries weren't great. The "chili" on them mostly tasted like tomato, and didn't have much meat or seasoning.
- The onion ring side wasn't as large as we expected for >$5.

detailedReviews.text: Wow !! We ate here last night.  We got the classic burger and it was FANTASTIC !!!!! The service was great - the food was great - we live in Orem and drove over to this place and now we will do it again and again !!

detailedReviews.author: kelton sumsion
detailedReviews.text: My experience at Wayback Burgers was the worst customer service I‚Äôve ever encountered. From the start, the staff was incredibly rude. The woman at the counter was dismissive and unhelpful. Despite only four people in the lobby, it took 45 minutes to get my food. When it finally arrived, several items were missing. I pointed this out, but she insisted everything was in the bag and refused to believe me until I unpacked it in front of her. Even then, she argued I hadn‚Äôt ordered the missing items‚Äîuntil I showed her my receipt. Reluctantly, she took another 15 minutes to bring the items. To top it off, I was still missing four of the six dipping sauces I ordered, and she called me ‚Äúneedy‚Äù when I asked for them. I will never return and wouldn‚Äôt recommend this place to anyone.

detailedReviews.author: Elizabeth DeVroom
detailedReviews.text: Chicken Bacon Ranch Bowl is now my new go to! Their shakes are amazing also! Great place with super friendly staff! It's clean and has a chill atmosphere.

detailedReviews.author: Klay Sevey
detailedReviews.text:
I had such a great experience at Wayback Burgers! From the moment I walked in, the staff was friendly and welcoming, and the restaurant felt clean and inviting. The food came out hot and fresh, and you can really tell everything is made to order.

The burgers are absolutely delicious‚Äîjuicy, perfectly seasoned, and packed with flavor. I love that they give you so many options to customize, from classic cheeseburgers to unique specialty creations. The buns were soft and fresh, and the toppings tasted really high-quality. I also ordered fries and a milkshake, and both were fantastic. The fries were golden and crispy, not greasy at all, and the milkshake was thick, creamy, and easily one of the best I‚Äôve had.

What stood out the most was how quick the service was without ever feeling rushed. The employees made sure everything was just right, and they even checked in to make sure I was happy with my meal. It really shows that they care about their customers.

Overall, Wayback Burgers delivers exactly what you‚Äôd hope for in a burger joint‚Äîgreat food, excellent service, and a relaxed atmosphere. I‚Äôll definitely be coming back and recommending it to friends and family!

detailedReviews.author: survivalist women
detailedReviews.text: Found this place right off the freeway, in Utah. Best experience, amazing service, amazing food. A must try.

detailedReviews.author: Kelson Shepherd
detailedReviews.text: Absolutely amazing burger and service! Will be back for sure!

detailedReviews.author: Branson Neff
detailedReviews.text:
I had the classic - loved it- great flavor!
The Cinnamon Toast Crunch milk shake is awesome!
We will back to eat there again.

detailedReviews.author: Dallin Largin
detailedReviews.text: Best burgers, shakes, and tots you will find. Hands down.

detailedReviews.author: Sean Dunlavy
detailedReviews.text: We went to Wayback burger on our way to see a play. It was delicious! I got the bourbon bacon burger. Man the flavor was so bold and delicious. I also got a side of tots which were crispy. Yum! Definitely give it a try you won‚Äôt be disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Matthew Huber
detailedReviews.text: I‚Äôm 53 years old. I‚Äôve learned to trust my own burgers when I want them. Every now and then I try a place to see if it works for me. Today I experienced Wayback burgers in Pleasant Grove Utah. It was an amazing experience!! I will struggle to grill my own burgers from now on. It was the best hamburger of my life. Their grind on the chuck is out of this world. The French fries are great and the sauces are perfectly balanced. The only thing I regret is not leaving room for a shake. Lesson learned, that won‚Äôt happen again! If you get a chance ask for Scott, he is the owner. He had high performance expectations regarding customer service.

detailedReviews.author: Spencer Ford
detailedReviews.text: Fantastic burger, will definitely get again. The standouts were the sides, best cheese curds around and great fried pickles.

detailedReviews.author: Destiny Schroeter
detailedReviews.text: Went there tonight. Their buns are so soft and yummy and their burgers are great! I will definitely be coming back to try their bowls and wraps and more burgers. Great prices for such an amazing burger.

detailedReviews.author: T James
detailedReviews.text: Delicious‚Ä¶.. thick juicy burger, fresh toppings, and soft bun. The sides were on point. Fried pickles, cheese curds, and fries. I‚Äôll be back soon!

detailedReviews.author: Jennifer James
detailedReviews.text: Food was delicious and fresh! Super friendly and clean. Food came out hot and quick. Saw Wayback burgers on IG and gave it a try, definitely will be back. Fried pickles were 100% on point!

detailedReviews.author: Ken Dinkel
detailedReviews.text: Quick service!  Burger and fries were great!

detailedReviews.author: Brandon Keele
detailedReviews.text: My wife and I tried this place tonight after recently moving to the area and it‚Äôs our new favorite place! The food was amazing, the atmosphere was fun, and the service was very nice and efficient. We will be back!

detailedReviews.author: Savanna Sng
detailedReviews.text: Great place for a good burger! I‚Äôll definitely be returning.

detailedReviews.author: Mark Tichenor

detailedReviews.author: Jacob Scott
detailedReviews.text: Friendly staff chatted with us and gave suggestions for their favorite items on the menu. We got the Cajun Burger and the classic burger.

detailedReviews.author: Haylin Martin
detailedReviews.text: I went with my husband the other night for more of a late night snack. We split a buffalo chicken sandwich and an Oreo shake. The chicken sandwich is probably the best chicken sandwich I‚Äôve ever had. The Oreo shake was tasty. The cream legitimately tasted like Oreo filling. Would definitely recommend this place to my friends.

detailedReviews.author: Kayla Yamagata
detailedReviews.text: The staff and expierence was absolutely amazing here, we had so much fun! But the food was not that great unfortunately. They went for some very niche sauces and even their plain burger was less than what I expected.

detailedReviews.author: Timothy D. Criswell

positive.author: Mimi Young
positive.text: Super nice employees and the food was really really tasty! It was my first time going but I'll definitely go back for sure!

positive.author: Tom Harker
positive.text:
I rolled up to Wayback Burgers thinking I could outsmart a burger by deconstructing it onto fries. Spoiler: the burger gods were not impressed.
The real MVP? The counter server who answered my ridiculous questions with saint-like patience and actually brought food to our table like some fast-food fairy godmother. In a world of ‚Äúorder 47, come get your sad meal,‚Äù this was refreshingly human.
My brilliant deconstructed burger experiment was‚Ä¶ fine. You know, ‚Äúfine‚Äù like your cousin‚Äôs potato salad ‚Äì edible but missing the magic. Turns out there‚Äôs a reason burgers come pre-assembled. Next time I‚Äôm trusting the engineers and ordering like a normal person.
But the chocolate brownie shake? Pure liquid regret. Despite reading warnings that it was sweeter than a rom-com and runnier than my gym excuses, I ordered it anyway. This shake was so thin I spent more time stirring than drinking, and sweet enough to cause diabetes through osmosis. Should‚Äôve gotten a soda and saved myself the disappointment.
The Verdict: Great service, decent burgers (if you don‚Äôt try to reinvent them), and shakes that are basically chocolate-flavored mistakes. Skip the liquid stuff, stick to the solids, and tip that counter angel and you may get the extra effort you paid for!

positive.author: Clint Decker
positive.text: Tasted amazing. Reasonable prices. I got the Cajun burger.

neutral.author: Taylor Brown
neutral.text: I had a great experience the first time I visited this place, which made me excited to return for my son's birthday. Unfortunately, our second visit didn‚Äôt live up to expectations. We were told there would be over an hour wait just to receive our food, and we saw several customers ahead of us getting refunds due to incorrect orders. With everything going on, we decided to leave. It‚Äôs disappointing, especially after such a positive first impression.

neutral.author: David Gould
neutral.text:
Brought the grease but lacked on flavor. I ordered a Cajun burger so I expected some kick but it wasn't there, patty was bland and brittle as well. Bottom bun was basically just a grease sponge. Ingredients were very fresh though.
Fries were top notch hot and crispy and salted nicely.

neutral.author: Samantha Leavitt
neutral.text: Burgers and shakes are great. We ordered a kids meal with 2 tenders fries were fine but the two chicken tenders we got were so small and burnt my kids barely got any food to eat. I tried adding a photo. I‚Äôm not a tender snob I promise.

negative.author: Brian Spencer
negative.text:
We ordered pickup here for my family of four. The burgers were good, but unfortunately there were more than a few hiccups:
- They nearly gave us the wrong order. We only noticed because the bag was way too small. Our receipt had been attached to the incorrect order.
- The burger for my two-year-old had an extra patty.
- One burger was supposed be plain but had everything on it.
- The chili cheese fries weren't great. The "chili" on them mostly tasted like tomato, and didn't have much meat or seasoning.
- The onion ring side wasn't as large as we expected for >$5.

negative.author: kelton sumsion
negative.text: My experience at Wayback Burgers was the worst customer service I‚Äôve ever encountered. From the start, the staff was incredibly rude. The woman at the counter was dismissive and unhelpful. Despite only four people in the lobby, it took 45 minutes to get my food. When it finally arrived, several items were missing. I pointed this out, but she insisted everything was in the bag and refused to believe me until I unpacked it in front of her. Even then, she argued I hadn‚Äôt ordered the missing items‚Äîuntil I showed her my receipt. Reluctantly, she took another 15 minutes to bring the items. To top it off, I was still missing four of the six dipping sauces I ordered, and she called me ‚Äúneedy‚Äù when I asked for them. I will never return and wouldn‚Äôt recommend this place to anyone.

negative.author: Jaxon davis
negative.text:
I placed an online order that was supposed to be ready by 7:15 for a Cajun burger, fries, and a shake. After waiting over an hour and asking about my food twice, they finally brought me an order‚Äîonly for it to be a lettuce wrap instead of my Cajun burger.

I took it back and asked for a refund, but the staff told me they didn‚Äôt know how to process one and promised to bring out the correct meal. Twenty minutes later, they gave me a Bourbon Burger instead. At this point, after nearly two hours of waiting, I just wanted my money back. Instead of a full refund, I was only given $10 for my $15 order.

Really disappointing experience. I won‚Äôt be coming back to this location.
